  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the cost to register a trademark in the U.S. varies depending on several factors, including the type of application you choose and the number of classes of goods or services you want to register under. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Application Types**: The United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) offers different application forms:\n   - **TEAS Plus**: $250 per class of goods/services. This option requires you to provide specific information upfront and meet certain requirements.\n   - **TEAS Standard**: $350 per class of goods/services. This is a more flexible application but comes with a higher fee.\n\n2. **Additional Costs**: \n   - If you need to respond to office actions or if your application faces opposition, there may be additional costs for legal assistance.\n   - If you want to register in multiple classes, the fees can add up quickly, as each class requires its own fee.\n\n3. **Legal Fees**: If you choose to hire an attorney to assist with the trademark registration process, this can add to your overall costs.\n\n4. **Maintenance Fees**: Once registered, there are also maintenance fees required at regular intervals to keep the trademark active.\n\nIt's important to check the USPTO website or consult a trademark attorney for the most current fees and procedures, as these can change over time.",
